    "body": "### Problem\n\nThere is a strange problem with expr folding with `vim.treesitter.foldexpr()` that happens when there is an autocommand at least on the `BufWinEnter` and `BufReadPost` events. It can be easily reproduced, as shown below.\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\nGiven the following `test.lua` file:\n\n```lua\nlocal root = vim.fn.fnamemodify(\"./nvim\", \":p\")\nfor _, name in ipairs({ \"config\", \"data\", \"state\", \"cache\" }) do\n  vim.env[(\"XDG_%s_HOME\"):format(name:upper())] = root .. \"/\" .. name\nend\nvim.opt.packpath:prepend(root .. \"data/nvim/site\")\nvim.pack.add({ \"https://github.com/nvim-treesitter/nvim-treesitter\" })\nvim.api.nvim_create_autocmd(\"PackChanged\", {\n  callback = function(ev)\n    local name, kind = ev.data.spec.name, ev.data.kind\n\n    if name == \"nvim-treesitter\" and kind == \"install\" or kind == \"update\" then\n      vim.cmd([[ TSUpdate ]])\n    end\n  end,\n})\nrequire(\"nvim-treesitter.configs\").setup({ ensure_installed = { \"yaml\" } })\n\n\nvim.api.nvim_create_autocmd({ \"BufWinEnter\", \"BufReadPost\" }, {\n  callback = function()\n    local _ = vim.fn.line(\"w0\")\n  end,\n})\n\n\nvim.opt.foldmethod = \"expr\"\nvim.opt.foldexpr = \"v:lua.vim.treesitter.foldexpr()\"\nvim.opt.foldcolumn = \"3\"\nvim.opt.foldlevel = 4\n```\n\nand the following `test.yml` file:\n\n```yaml\n\nfoo:\n  bar:\n    - name: Bar one in foo\n      property: a bar\n\n    - name: Bar two in foo\n      property: a bar\n  baz:\n    - name: Baz one in foo\n      property: a bar\n\n    - name: Baz two in foo\n      property: a bar\n```\n\n0. Create the files in some test directory. I'll assume the following commands are run in that directory.\n1. `nvim --clean -u test.lua test.yml`\n2. `yyjjppppp` - copy the first (empty) line, move down two lines, paste it repeatedly\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nThe fold regions should \"move\" accordingly. But they don't. It is best explained with a couple of screenshots. The first one shows how I _expect_ it to look:\n\n<img width=\"350\" height=\"440\" alt=\"Image\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/b5c15d5d-5276-4244-8207-0dbb294ce2fa\" />\n\nThe next one is the observed result:\n\n<img width=\"366\" height=\"451\" alt=\"Image\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/556506d7-170d-4a00-9ed4-33c402aed1e0\" />\n\nNotice that I get the expected result if I remove the autocmd. Also, for some reason, the `zx` and `zX` mappings don't work - the folds do not recompute properly. They _do_ work if I remove the autocmd (then there are sometimes minor glitches that can be fixed with `zx`).\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\nNVIM v0.12.0-dev-1679+g10c11c4644\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nNot relevant\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nArch Linux\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nwezterm 20251123-154500-ac08cdf6\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nxterm-256color\n\n### Installation\n\nAUR",
